searchengine

Class IndexBenchmark

  • java.lang.Object
    • searchengine.IndexBenchmark

  • public class IndexBenchmark
extends java.lang.Object
    The Indexing benchmark. This prototype benchmarks the efficiency of the search engine's index by querying it multiple times and taking time measurements. The benchmark is implemented with JMH, which e.g. takes care of warming up the JVM. It is in part inspired by BenchmarkModes and States in the JMH Samples. This does not start a web server.
    See Also:
    JMH, JMH Samples, JMH Annotations Documentation

      • measureAvgTime

        public void measureAvgTime(IndexBenchmark.BenchmarkState state)
                    throws java.lang.InterruptedException
        Measures the average execution time of this method. How it works: JMH continuously calls this method in a fixed (rather long) window of time, measures the time each method call took, and counts how many times the method was called. JMH then uses this data to compute the average execution time.
        Throws:
        java.lang.InterruptedException

        JMH-magic. This needs to be here, but this main is actually never run. JMH generates lots of other classes, and then runs those instead.
